<!--
    PUF France Use Case 22a: Early Payment Discount - Services Invoice (VAT on Cash Receipt)

    Business Scenario:
    - Consulting firm (SELLER) provides IT consulting services for 10,000 EUR HT + 20% VAT
    - Invoice offers 2% early payment discount (escompte) if paid within 10 days
    - The discount amount does NOT appear on the invoice - only the conditions are mentioned
    - Invoice is issued for the full amount (no discount deducted)

    Key UC22a Mechanism:
    - VAT is due on cash receipt (services, à l'encaissement)
    - The discount is reflected in the "Cashed" (Encaissée) lifecycle status
    - The "Encaissée" status declares the amount actually received (TTC minus discount)
    - No credit note is needed - the administration sees the actual amount via lifecycle status

    Mandatory Discount Mention:
    - BT-21 = AAB (Conditions of sale)
    - BT-22 = Discount conditions text
    - This mention is MANDATORY even when no discount is offered (in that case: "Néant")

    Worked Example:
    - Total HT (BT-109): 10,000.00 EUR
    - Total VAT (BT-110) @ 20%: 2,000.00 EUR
    - Total TTC (BT-112): 12,000.00 EUR
    - Amount Due (BT-115): 12,000.00 EUR (full amount, discount not yet applied)
    - If BUYER takes discount: pays 11,760.00 EUR (12,000 - 240 = 2% of TTC)
    - "Encaissée" status amount: 11,760.00 EUR

    Source: XP Z12-014 Annexe A v1.3, Section 3.2.20
-->
<Invoice xmlns="urn:pagero:PageroUniversalFormat:Invoice:1.0" xmlns:cac="urn:pagero:CommonAggregateComponents:1.0" xmlns:cbc="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonBasicComponents-2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:puf="urn:pagero:ExtensionComponent:1.0" xmlns:ext="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonExtensionComponents-2">

